node.text:
The new Defender is arguably the most anticipated car of 2020, bringing the Defender into the modern era by applying the latest technology available from Land Rover. The upgrades are instantly apparent. From its modern edgy style to the series of onboard computers and stability systems, the new Defender is without a doubt a change for the better. Incorporating computers into everything the Defender does makes for a much more refined driver experience over the previous analogue drive. The long suspension travel provides a soft and gentle ride, absorbing any imperfection in the terrain beneath it. Although it shows good on-road compliance, it is just as impressive off-road, easily navigating through any terrain with the clever Dynamic Stability Control and all-wheel drive system.

The Defender 90 model arrived in late 2020, featuring a shorter wheelbase compared to the 110, providing maximum agility on and off the road. The ‘X’ variant is the top of the line spec, providing you with many of the usually costing options as standard. This means the Defender is fully packed with technology inside and out – everything you could ever need for adventures on and off the road. This particular example has the highest power output engine, providing the necessary power on demand and when required. The new Defender has truly been redefined, whilst still demonstrating the original purpose of what the Land Rover Defender was originally designed to achieve.

node.title: Which New Land Rover Defender Should You Buy?

node.text:
In this video, Tom Jaconelli gives you expert advice about the differences between the three Porsche Taycan models, the 4S, the Turbo and the top of the range Turbo S!

The Porsche Taycan Turbo, which translates to 'Spirited Young Horse’ in Turkish, is Porsche's first fully electric vehicle after the highly praised Mission E concept. The Porsche Taycan Turbo offers a sleek, elegant and futuristic design in appearance, in keeping with other Porsche model features and harnesses technologies from the Le Mans-winning 919 race car, which becomes evident in the performance data.

The Taycan Turbo executes a 0-62 time in 3.2 seconds and will continue to 99mph in 6.9 seconds. These figures are extremely impressive considering the Taycan Turbo has a weight of around 2,305kg (unladen) due to the front and rear motors and batteries. Cornering speed is no issue either due to the batteries sitting low in the car, providing a low centre of gravity. The power steering is equally impressive and provides the driver with a direct feel to the road, providing you with the maximum level of confidence.

Along with high performance, comfort comes paramount with any Porsche model. The Taycan Turbo is no exception to this. The ride feel is smooth and as silent as you need it to be, which is just one of the benefits of electric vehicles. Porsche Stability Management (PSM) and the Adaptive Air Suspension give you a plush ride, dealing with bumps and road imperfections perfectly. The Taycan Turbo is a well rounded electric saloon that offers confidence inspiring and rewarding handling with fast charging times and ample driving range, providing more power than its 4S sibling.

node.title: Porsche Taycan - Choosing Between The 4S, Turbo & Turbo S!

In our latest video, Tom guides you through the 10 best things you can find in this private jet for the road, the Mercedes-Maybach S600 Pullman!

2018 Mercedes-Maybach S 600 Pullman For Sale:
https://www.romansinternational.com/u...

The Pullman name has been derived from its original use where an American car company manufactured railway carriages with luxurious, open-plan cabins. This was then applied to long wheelbase Mercedes vehicles with generously sized passenger compartments. Over the years the name has promoted the very best of luxury offered by Mercedes.

The Mercedes-Maybach S 600 Pullman represents the highest level of exclusivity and individuality in the Mercedes range, providing spaciousness and comfort like no other. The S 600 Pullman pushes the boundaries of the luxury vehicle category, with a limousine that commands authority on the road with its 6.5 metre length, which also makes rear cabin seating for 4 in comfort and style possible. This 3000kg behemoth provides the pinnacle of comfort through an imaginative design that is rarely seen within the industry.

Designed for VIP occupants the S 600 Pullman comes equipped with ample options as standard, focusing on passenger comfort with standard features including Multicontour rear seats and rear seat entertainment. Overall, the Mercedes-Maybach S 600 exceeds the expectations of exclusivity and luxury, providing occupants with more than what is required for the highest level of luxury.

node.title: The 10 Best Things About The Mercedes-Maybach S600 Pullman!

In this video Tom gives an in depth guide to the spec and options to look out for when buying a Mercedes AMG GT R. From paint choices to carbon fibre trim packs to driver assistance systems, this guide gives you everything you need to know when purchasing an AMG GT R.

Check out our current range of AMG GT cars for sale via our website!

The AMG GT R is nicknamed the 'Beast of The Green Hell' and it has quickly become one of the most desirable supercars on the market. Thoroughly developed from the ground up by AMG, the GT R has become a serious contender to the likes of the more expensive Ferrari 458 Speciale, McLaren 675LT and recently the Lamborghini Huracan Performante. Like all of these limited-edition supercars the AMG GT R is a track focused supercar built for the road.

The GT R has several highlight unique features over the GT S variant including increased power to 577bhp, massive carbon fibre rear-wing to compliment the active aerodynamics and is also the first Mercedes-AMG to feature rear-axle steering. A new central dial labelled “TC” allows the driver to choose from the 11 different traction control settings, allowing the driver to build confidence and gradually explore the cars full potential, depending on experience and conditions.

Even with the use of turbochargers the 4.0L V8 must be one of the best sounding V8s on the market with its triple exit exhaust offering distinctly raucous AMG notes. Offering high levels of driver convenience and technology combined with brutal pace and track capability, as proved when it broke the Nürburgring production car lap record, the AMG GT R provides a well-rounded package and really does offer huge value for money when compared with its Italian competition.

node.title: The Definitive AMG GTR Buying Guide

Viva Italia 🇮🇹
It's the Alfa Romeo Giulia Quadrifoglio! One of the best performance saloons out there the QV has bags of character in a very affordable price range.

Now if you know about these cars you should know that the coolest and most desirable option on this car is the Sparco Carbon Fibre Shell Racing Seats. They would have cost the original owner £3,250 and for that reason its very hard to find an example with them.

This car also has the tri-colour paint Competizione Red which is fully protected with PPF applied to the whole car. With lots of other options equipped too and only 1,672 miles covered, if you are ever going to buy a Giulia Quadrifoglio then this is the one you should want!

#AlfaRomeo #GiuliaQuadrifoglio #CompetizioneRed #Alfaholic #Passione #SparcoSeats #ExceptionalExamples

node.text:
The forgotten one? The Velar SVAutobiography might be the lesser known of the performance Range Rovers built by Land Rover Special Operations but what a little package this is. 

The 5.0L Supercharged V8 giving you the noise and power befitting of most Supercars and all in a practical 5 seater and actually one of the rarest SUVs out there. 

This example features the 1600W Meridian Signature Sound System and with only 5,654 miles on the clock this is one of the most desirable ones around. 

A daily driver with some punch or just a fun addition to the fleet which should fit the whole family the Velar SVAutobiography is a niche but one that makes a strong argument to fit the bill.

#VelarSVAutobiography #RangeRoverSVO #V8 #ARareSight #SmallPackage #BigPerformance

node.text:
Rosso Barchetta 599 GTO🍒.
Only 1,530 miles. UK supplied right drive car. We believe this to be one of the most special 599 GTO’s to come to market in recent years.

Having sold this car to a private collector back in 2013 we were delighted to have the opportunity to buy this back and offer it for sale once again.

A truly unique example thanks to its 2 layer extracampionario paint “Rosso Barchetta” which is a darker and deeper red than the standard Rosso Corsa. This is set off by the GTO’s signature Grigio Silverstone Opaco roof and optioned with the highly desirable full carbon fibre side sills. This car has then been beautifully combined with a Charcoal Alcantara interior with several options and features over and above the standard specification.

Rarer than both the F12tdf and 812 Competizione the 599 GTO is a V12 Ferrari that deserves to be in every important Ferrari collection and what an opportunity with this example to own such a low mileage and unique spec car!

#599GTO #RossoBarchetta #SpecialPaint #SpecialCar #V12 #NaturallyAspirated #FutureClassic #Collectible #Ferrari #ExceptionalExamples #RomansInternational
